I am addicted to Thai food and I get my regular fix is La's Thai. This time, we were around Chandler mall and wanted to try a new place. Though a bit pricey, the food was great and the portions are huge. I got Drunken noodles triple Thai hot and my wife got an Thai iced tea and Panang Tofu and we shared the vegetable tempura. The food was amazing...Panang Tofu was a bit flat but I have to blame myself as I didn't take the waitress' suggestion. By the time we were done, the owner came in and talked to us and gave a breif history of the foods we just had and asked us to watch the football game with him... I loved everything about the place...good food, friendly and attentive waitress and overall feeling that we are welcome at the place...  I am keeping one start till I try couple more things.

